<section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-8">
  <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-6">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">Dashboard Overview</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
      The Dashboard is the central hub of your author account. It provides a comprehensive
      overview of all your content, audience engagement, and performance metrics in one place.
      This page allows you to quickly assess the health of your blog and make data-driven decisions.
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4 mt-4">
      <div class="p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700">Blog Count</h3>
        <p class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-2">Total number of articles you have published, including drafts and scheduled posts.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700">Views</h3>
        <p class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-2">Shows how many times your posts have been read. Helps track popular content.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700">Shares</h3>
        <p class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-2">Indicates how often readers are sharing your content on social media, helping gauge reach.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700">Comments</h3>
        <p class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-2">Displays engagement from your readers. More comments mean higher interaction and connection with your audience.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Performance Graphs</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600">
        Visual charts that show trends over time, such as views per post, monthly traffic, and top-performing articles.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800">Purpose of the Dashboard</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mt-2">
          The Dashboard helps you monitor the success of your content in real-time. By tracking metrics like views, shares, and comments, you can identify what resonates with your audience. This insight allows you to focus on high-performing topics, optimize your posting schedule, and grow your readership.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800">Why Each Section Matters</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>Blog Count ensures you know how active you are as a creator and helps plan your publishing strategy.</li>
          <li>Views give insight into overall audience interest.</li>
          <li>Shares expand your content’s reach outside the platform.</li>
          <li>Comments provide qualitative feedback, helping you engage with readers directly.</li>
          <li>Performance Graphs help visualize trends, detect spikes or drops in engagement, and optimize content accordingly.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
